      "latex": "\\mathbf{H}_{ij}=\\frac{\\partial\\left(f(\\mathbf{x})/\\partial x_{i}\\right)}{\\partial x_{j}}=\\frac{\\partial^{2}f(\\mathbf{x})}{\\partial x_{i}\\partial x_{j}}",
      "label": "Formula A6.13",
      "chapter_id": "appendix6",
      "section": "Appendix: Introduction",
      "subsection": "THE HESSIAN MATRIX, LOCAL MAXIMA/MINIMA, AND MULTIDIMENSIONAL TAYLOR SERIES",
      "position": 12,
      "depth": 0,
      "context_text": "Note that this is the outer product of $ \\nabla_{\\mathbf{x}} [f] $ with itself. Recall for an $ n $-dimensional column vector $ \\mathbf{a}_{n\\times1} $ that while the inner product, $ \\mathbf{a}_{1\\times n}^T \\mathbf{a}_{n\\times1} = \\sum a_i $, returns a $ 1 \\times 1 $ matrix (a scalar), the outer product, $ \\mathbf{a}_{n\\times1} \\mathbf{a}_{1\\times n}^T $, returns an $ n \\times n $ matrix whose $ ij $th element is $ a_i a_j $, or (in our case)",
